items.title: No September jobs report, no problem. Here’s what we know about the labor market — and it’s not great.
items.description: Hiring has slowed to a crawl, and there’s no sign it will pick up soon.

items.title: Jobs in service sector shrink for fourth month on tariff uncertainty, lack of qualified workers
items.description: Service sector stalls while price pressures intensify, putting the Federal Reserve in a tough spot.

items.title: ‘I don’t come from money’: I received $1.2 million after a family tragedy. Am I foolish to keep it in a money-market account?
items.description: “Having a large sum just sitting there freaks me out.”

items.title: Why the bad news that sank Zillow’s stock is good for new investors
items.description: An analyst who has been neutral on Zillow’s stock for years just turned bullish after the recent selloff, saying it now offers potential 20% upside.

items.title: ‘We’re in a market bubble’: I’m 62 and single. I want to move my $200K IRA to a money-market account. Am I mad?
items.description: “I will also draw Social Security when I reach 70, which will be $3,500 per month.”
